I’m gonna start keeping up with bond signals to help me determine overall macro equity trends. Charted the 10Y US bond yield and I think overall market can sustain being bullish for another couple months. After which the breakout on bond yields can trigger a market correction and sector rotation from growth to value stocks. 

10Y yield is currently trading in an Elliot Wave ABCDE pattern. Just topped off the (D) today headed for (E) formation expected to bottom out around March 2022, which is the final downtrend before a massive breakout in bond yields (similar pattern is also seen with the 30Y US yield). The timing of the breakout from my technical analysis also perfectly aligns with Fed QE reversal👀.
